cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.Distributed, cs.OS, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the WebSocket protocol and its use for real-time communication in web browsers. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of WebSocket for distributed computing. 
- cs.Distributed is another possible category as the paper focuses on the use of WebSocket for distributed computing and real-time communication. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is a possible category as the paper discusses different WebSocket server implementations and their performance. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses a new promising library for WebSocket.
